Text.Value: They belong to the clan. They're coming with us.
It's time I scram, before the buggers at Moonrise charge in.
Set them free, or I will thrash you like I thrashed Nere.
Yeah, right. No chance we're letting those bastards take the gnomes with them. Right?
What makes Moonrise Towers such a threat?
And the slaves? What about them?

EditorData.logicalname: At least one gnome still alive

Text.Value: You're free, squatties. Get your legs moving, before I change my damn mind.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general

Text.Value: Damn right. We'll keep them busy - this isn't their last dig.
Some General up there giving the orders, the way Nere told it.
Good idea. I'll start by adding your corpse to the pile.
Figured you wouldn't.
Leave.
Go on, then. Been itching to cut you down a peg.
You might be right about that. The more bodies we got, the slower we move.
My pocket's been picked. Try the cadavers - probably loaded with loot.
Your heart made of stone? They deserved freedom - and you denied it.
Leave - and take the slaves with you. Before I change my mind.
Here's your cut. Just like Brithvar said. ([6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Understood. I won't interfere.
The gnomes should be able to go where they please. They are not the duergar's to keep.
They got goblins, drow, gnolls, even humans - ain't no one they won't try to turn. The clans included.
Get moving. If I see you slavers again, I'll tear you apart.
Shit. Brithvar's kicked the tankard. Prick was older than dirt.
Speak up, chief. You can't just let the clan keep them.
Whoa. Who the fuck are you?
Very well. I'll rummage what I can.
These shitheads aren't worth the hassle. You got yourself a deal.
Place is swarming with Absolute-buggers. And I ain't gonna mess about with 'em.
Free the gnomes or DIE. You choose.
The gnomes go free. You live. Everyone wins. Clear?
And the gold you owe me?

EditorData.logicalname: Didn't have enough gold - needs flag

Text.Value: You drugnin' twat.
Good idea. They're a valuable asset.
You think? I catch so much as a whiff of you, and I'll have you flayed and fried up for dinner.
Let the gnomes go. They'll just slow you down.
Brittle are the foundations upon which the houses of tyrants are built. It seems I judged you to be less brittle than you really are.
Get to it then.
Now move out of here - I got shit to be doing.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general.

Text.Value: I am freeing these gnomes. Just try and stop me.
Nah. They slow us down, I hold fire to their arses. You should see 'em dance!
Here's your cut. Half the spoils, like Brithvar said. ([463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
Listen up, Clan Flameshade - we need to cut and run.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.logicalname: at least one other rebel still alive.

Text.Value: You don't need to ask twice, jargh.

Synopsis: The mutinous duergar is dead, so another takes his place to tells you they are moving on
